calculator

Class InterpreterTest

  • java.lang.Object
    • calculator.InterpreterTest

  • public class InterpreterTest
extends java.lang.Object
    This tests the basic version of the parser. It tests some basic expressions without lambdas or lets. To run this test you have to create a class named explang.interpret.Interpreter This class should have a static method named "run" which takes a String, parses and evaluates it and returns the result of the evaluation as an int.
